sec-intl.segmenter.supportedlocalesof.summary: The Intl.Segmenter.supportedLocalesOf() static method returns an array containing those of the provided locales that are supported without having to fall back to the runtime's default locale.
sec-intl.segmenter.supportedlocalesof.title: Intl.Segmenter.supportedLocalesOf()

segmenter-objects.name: Segmenter
segmenter-objects.summary: The Intl.Segmenter object enables locale-sensitive text segmentation, enabling you to get meaningful items (graphemes, words or sentences) from a string.
segmenter-objects.title: Intl.Segmenter

sec-%segmentsprototype%.containing.name: containing
sec-%segmentsprototype%.containing.summary: The containing() method of Segments instances returns an object describing the segment in the string that includes the code unit at the specified index.
sec-%segmentsprototype%.containing.title: Segments.prototype.containing()

sec-%segmentsprototype%-@@iterator.name: @@iterator
sec-%segmentsprototype%-@@iterator.summary: The [@@iterator]() method of Segments instances implements the iterable protocol and allows Segments objects to be consumed by most syntaxes expecting iterables, such as the spread syntax and for...of loops. It returns an segments iterator object that yields data about each segment.
sec-%segmentsprototype%-@@iterator.title: Segments.prototype[@@iterator]()

sec-segments-objects.name: Segments
sec-segments-objects.summary: A Segments object is an iterable collection of the segments of a text string. It is returned by a call to the segment() method of an Intl.Segmenter object.
sec-segments-objects.title: Segments

sec-intl.getcanonicallocales.name: getCanonicalLocales
sec-intl.getcanonicallocales.summary: The Intl.getCanonicalLocales() static method returns an array containing the canonical locale names. Duplicates will be omitted and elements will be validated as structurally valid language tags.
sec-intl.getcanonicallocales.title: Intl.getCanonicalLocales()

sec-intl.supportedvaluesof.name: supportedValuesOf
sec-intl.supportedvaluesof.summary: The Intl.supportedValuesOf() static method returns an array containing the supported calendar, collation, currency, numbering systems, or unit values supported by the implementation.
sec-intl.supportedvaluesof.title: Intl.supportedValuesOf()

sec-Intl-toStringTag.name: @@toStringTag
sec-Intl-toStringTag.summary: The Intl namespace object contains several constructors as well as functionality common to the internationalization constructors and other language sensitive functions. Collectively, they comprise the ECMAScript Internationalization API, which provides language sensitive string comparison, number formatting, date and time formatting, and more.
sec-Intl-toStringTag.title: Intl

intl-object.name: Intl
intl-object.summary: The Intl namespace object contains several constructors as well as functionality common to the internationalization constructors and other language sensitive functions. Collectively, they comprise the ECMAScript Internationalization API, which provides language sensitive string comparison, number formatting, date and time formatting, and more.
intl-object.title: Intl

sup-number.prototype.tolocalestring.name: toLocaleString
sup-number.prototype.tolocalestring.summary: The toLocaleString() method returns a string with a language-sensitive representation of this number. In implementations with Intl.NumberFormat API support, this method simply calls Intl.NumberFormat.

ie.notes: In Internet Explorer 11, numbers are rounded to 15 decimal digits. For example, (1000000000000005).toLocaleString('en-US') returns "1,000,000,000,000,010".

sup-number.prototype.tolocalestring.title: Number.prototype.toLocaleString()

sup-String.prototype.localeCompare.name: localeCompare
sup-String.prototype.localeCompare.summary: The localeCompare() method returns a number indicating whether a reference string comes before, or after, or is the same as the given string in sort order. In implementations with Intl.Collator API support, this method simply calls Intl.Collator.
sup-String.prototype.localeCompare.title: String.prototype.localeCompare()

sup-string.prototype.tolocalelowercase.name: toLocaleLowerCase
sup-string.prototype.tolocalelowercase.summary: The toLocaleLowerCase() method returns the calling string value converted to lower case, according to any locale-specific case mappings.
sup-string.prototype.tolocalelowercase.title: String.prototype.toLocaleLowerCase()

sup-string.prototype.tolocaleuppercase.name: toLocaleUpperCase
sup-string.prototype.tolocaleuppercase.summary: The toLocaleUpperCase() method returns the calling string value converted to upper case, according to any locale-specific case mappings.
sup-string.prototype.tolocaleuppercase.title: String.prototype.toLocaleUpperCase()
